The paper deals with a data structure problem related to sets of real numbers, which suggests categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The problem involves efficiently computing the sign of the sum of any triple of numbers, which is a combinatorial problem that could fall under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper discusses the use of word-RAM, which is a computational model that could be relevant to cs.DL (Digital Libraries).
